關於該職缺

Operations Services & Excellence Associate


Farmacy is a green-living and urban agriculture tech company with a purpose on social impact. We develop data-driven farming systems and cloud-based solutions, empowering people to address food security, fresh food supplies, and carbon emission challenges in highly urbanised cities across the globe.


We are the winner of major technology and innovation awards, including but not limited to:
  • 2024 Vertical Farming World Award
  • 2023 APEC Awards the First Bio-Circular-Green Prize
  • 2023 Smart City Grand Awards of Hong Kong Design Association
  • 2022 Hong Kong ICT Startup Awards (Grand Award and Social Impact Gold Award)
  • 2021 City I&T Grand Challenge Hong Kong (Innovation Award)


Based in Hong Kong, Farmacy operates across 5 sectors, covering 40+ sites in retail, food (restaurant & hospitality), land development, education and public communities. On top of supplying green produces with 100% freshness and nutrition intake, we work with market leaders to drive measurable ESG impacts through reducing 30% food waste, 70% carbon emission on transportation, and 90% water usage.


We are expanding into overseas markets, including Australia, UAE, Thailand, and more.



Key information

Available for: Business / Operations Management with university degree(s)

Job Function: Operations Services & Excellence

Type of Employment: Full Time (5-day work)

Location: Hong Kong, with travel requirement



Role & Responsibilities

We are seeking a detail-oriented Operations Services & Excellence Associate to support production planning and enhance operational efficiency. This role requires a proactive individual with strong organizational skills and a commitment to customer service.


Production Planning:
  • Assist in the development and execution of production plans to meet customer demands and optimize resource utilization.
  • Collaborate with production and supply chain teams to ensure timely delivery of products.


Client Engagement:
  • Maintain strong relationships with clients, addressing inquiries and providing updates on project / production status.
  • Gather and analyse client feedback to inform planning processes.


Operational Support:
  • Monitor production schedules and workflows to identify potential issues and implement solutions.
  • Support the development of process improvements to enhance operational efficiency.


Data Analysis:
  • Analyse production data to track performance metrics and identify trends.
  • Prepare reports for management on production planning and operational performance.


Team Collaboration:
  • Work closely with cross teams to ensure alignment on production goals and client expectations.
  • Participate in team meetings to share insights and contribute to operational strategies.



Experience / Skills Requirements
  • bachelor’s degree in business, operations management, or a related field preferred.
  • 2+ years of experience in operations, production planning, or a similar role.
  • strong analytical skills with proficiency in data analysis tools
  • excellent communication and interpersonal skills
  • ability to work collaboratively in a fast-paced environment
  • fluent in English and Chinese (Mandarin & Cantonese)


Why Farmacy?
  • participate in hackdays and growth days from day one
  • a steep learning-curve – personally and professionally
  • opportunities of working with managers / decision makers of top tier clients and partners
  • good exposure to wide range of industries / sectors
  • a lively startup atmosphere with friendly working culture
  • able to see results driven by your efforts



W: www.farmacyhk.com I E: talent@farmacyhk.com I Facebook / Instagram: #farmacyhk

關於本公司

FarmacyHK
1,452 人關注
餐飲製造 11-50 位員工 15 位員工在 LinkedIn

Farmacy is a green smart-living tech company with a purpose on impact: we are driving a new green movement with our unique decentralised and data-driven farm technologies.

Building smart mobile farms everywhere in the city, covering supermarkets, restaurants, hotels, malls, residential clubhouses, offices, and schools, our partners are empowered to grow what they want and harvest what they need onsite through Farmacy’s cloud-based farming system. Together we reduce 30% food waste and 70% carbon emission on transportation while gaining 100% freshness and nutrition intake.

We are the winner of several major technology and innovation awards, including City I&T Grand Challenge Hong Kong 2021 (Innovation Award), FHKI Startup Council STAR Programme 2021 (Most Popular Startup Award), Qianhai Guangdong-Hong Kong-Macao-Taiwan Youth Innovation and Entrepreneurship Competition 2020 (Bronze Medal), and AsiaProp Tech 2018 (Champion). ⋯⋯
